             depos'd, That it was his Business to cut the Wood, and a Stick of about 3 Quarters of a Hundred was damag'd and rotten, and good for little, and that tho' he had work'd for him Several years, yet he never knew that he bought any Logwood but of the Salter, and paid him for Cutting it by the Salter's Bill. He call'd several to his Reputation, who gave him a good Character. The Jury <rs id="t17240226-64-verdict325" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17240226-64-verdict325" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
